\section{Title}

---> Alu can be co-opted as useful sequence since they don't have any large detrimental effects on the system (unlike L1). This would allow them to be maintained in the genome under neutral-esque conditions.

--> Talk about variability between humans and missing heritability and how RTs can be responsible for some of this missing heritability

---> Talk about the use of RTs in GWAS type studies. 

---> Talk about somatic retrotransposition and how that can lead to variation within a human

---> Talk about retinoic acid response elements within Alu and how that might be contributing to the difference in expression between the sexes (especially RORA1)

